result.execSummary:
The defendant Regina Michelle Price was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Regina Michelle Price is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Regina Michelle Price was found guilty of Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).
  • Regina Michelle Price was found guilty of Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Attorney Amanda K Tisdale in court for Regina Michelle Price.  Attorney Lisa A. Riniker in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Regina Michelle Price in court. Per agreement, State moves to amend Ct 2 to possession of meth. Defendant will plead to amended Ct 2 and Ct 3 and State will move to dismiss Cts 1 and 4. State will recommend 3 years probation with the following conditions: to participate in counseling that DOC deems appropriate, submit to random drug tests, 60 days jail, and to pay court costs. Court grants amendment to Ct 2. Court reviews plea questionnaire and finds defendant freely and knowingly waives rights. Defendant pleads n o contest. Court accepts plea and finds defendant guilty of Cts 2 and 3. Court dismisses Cts 1 and 4 on State's motion. Court reviews rights lost due to felony conviction. State heard. Attorney Tisdale heard. Defendant heard. Court heard and orders 3 years probation with the following conditions: not to possess or consume any controlled substances unless prescribed and to be taken only as prescribed, not to possess or consume any alcohol, submit to random, observed testing for controlled substances and alcohol upon request of law enforcement, DOC, or designee, engage in a program of treatment for controlled substance abuse and addiction, to have such assessment, counseling, treatment, and programming that DOC deems appropriate, court costs, and DNA. 3 days credit if revoked. Court sets a probation review hearing to check on defendant's progress and will difemerine then if jail time is needed.
